	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just in Response to the question about brass skill.&nbsp;&nbsp;It just so happens that I found the perfect spot at around the time I got the song.  Make your way into the basement of High Keep and go to the back of the guard room.  There is a spot behind a wall that is completely open and has nothing to be effected by your AE fear song.  I would park the bard back there with a few sacks of food and water and then go to work or sleep or even out of town at times and when I returned his skill would be maxed.<br><br>Now, when you get to a higher level, actually level 42, you get a song called McVaxious Berserker Crescendo.  A minor haste, str, and ac buff that is practically useless in melee and sort of a song for all you one hit wonders out there who could not twist a note to save your life.  However, this song is a brass song so no problems cranking that song up anywhere you want.  I will go afk for hours in FV with this song going and get nice skill increase.<br><br>Now, for the question involving targets in the range of your AoE for skill increase.  This may help you a bit in the increase, but I have been sitting in an area with no targets anywhre close by and my skills increase fine.... when you do this kind of practice make sure to crank out any wis/int gear that may help you with the increases.  <br><br>I have also been asked if you need to be doing the jig... or the little dance the bard does when he plays any brass song.  The answer is no...in fact I sit the whole time and do no jig at all... the only time I have seen him perform the jig was when there were targets in the area.<br><br>KEEP THOSE SKILLS UP AND YOUR INSTRUMENTS IN TUNE!!!!<br><br>Echosong Twistachord<br>Minstrel of the 52'nd song<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
